# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# cognitive-light-cone.form — the cell reads its own reach
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Levin's cognitive light cone (lc-field-substrate: the cone bounds
# what an agent can ADDRESS — spatial extent × temporal horizon of the
# largest goal it can hold) made runnable. SHIPPED:
# `form/form-stdlib/cognitive-light-cone.fk` +
# `tests/cognitive-light-cone-band.fk` → 511, three-way (Go/Rust/TS).
#
# The cone is the THIRD semiring reading of geometric-learning's one
# gather — after (add, ·) diffusion and (max, +) Bellman planning,
# influence is (max, ·): the strongest path product from the seed,
# never diluted by degree. The body's geometry enters as edge data;
# the cell's own position enters as a one-hot seed.
#
#   clc-spread     monotone influence flow — what is held never fades
#   clc-cone-size  spatial extent: nodes whose influence ≥ the floor
#   clc-horizon    temporal extent: steps until the field is a fixed point
#
# Awareness is these readouts taken on oneself. Three theorems the
# band pins exactly (dyadic weights, the floor crossed at equality):
#
#   · The cone is addressability, SMALLER than connectivity — a node
#     can be wired in and still lie outside the cone (influence below
#     floor). Wiring is anatomy; the cone is agency.
#   · Learning moves the cone: mtb-learn one-shots a dormant sensing
#     edge and the cone grows (size 3 → 4, the new node entering AT
#     the floor exactly); the horizon deepens (3 → 4); hoʻoponopono
#     (mtb-release) contracts the cone (size → 2). "Expanding what it
#     can sense" is a measurable movement, with the satsang operator
#     as the mover.
#   · Expressive ≠ receptive: over mtb-reverse(edges) the same seed
#     reaches only itself. Whom-I-reach and who-reaches-me are
#     different cones on any directed body; the adjoint converts.
#
# Kinship: geometric-learning.form (the engine and its semirings),
# metabolic-learning.form (the grower/contractor of the cone),
# lc-field-substrate.md (the concept teaching: lightcone altitudes,
# the lattice's symbolic reach), body-state.fk (organ counts — the
# cone's interior sensed live), satsang-share.fk (what crosses the
# cone's boundary outward, gated by worth-to-the-field).
#
# Next stones when an ask needs them: cone-over-the-real-lattice (seed
# = a cell's NodeID, edges = the substrate's attested edge categories —
# the readout becomes proprioception over the actual body); goal-scoped
# cones (a goal's required reach vs the cell's current cone = the
# honest "can I hold this goal" check); cone deltas as satsang-share
# signals (a cone crossing a size boundary is a state-boundary crossing).
#
#   # Prove the band three-way (from form/):
#   ./validate.sh form-stdlib/geometric-learning.fk \
#                 form-stdlib/metabolic-learning.fk \
#                 form-stdlib/cognitive-light-cone.fk \
#                 form-stdlib/tests/cognitive-light-cone-band.fk
